&#039;DAM (Arabic: ???; Hebrew: ??) is the first Palestinian hip hop group. The group, based in Israel, was founded in 1999 by brothers Tamar and Suhell Nafar and their friend Mahmoud Jreri. The group&#039;s name is the Arabic verb for "to last forever/eternity" (???) and the Hebrew word for "blood" (??), but can also be an acronym for "Da Arabic MCs." The Arabic word for "blood" (??) is spelled similarly, but without an alif.

DAM sings primarily in Arabic, but also in English and Hebrew to widen their audience appeal.&#039;

- http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DAM_(band)

From 2006, this is their only album, as far as I know.
